# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and configure the values for your local development.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

## Required Variables

None required - all have sensible defaults

## Optional Variables

### Site Configuration

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` | Base URL for the website (used in metadata, sitemap, robots.txt) | `https://youtube-connector-mcp-website.vercel.app` |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_REPO_URL` | GitHub repository URL (used in JSON-LD) | `https://github.com/ShellyDeng08/youtube-connector-mcp` |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTHOR_NAME` | Author name (used in metadata and JSON-LD) | `xuelian.deng` |

### Deployment

On Vercel, these are set automatically:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` - Set to the deployed URL

For custom domains or different deployment targets, override accordingly.
